(4, 1, '2017-03-18 00:10:06', '2017-03-18 00:10:06', '<p style="text-align: left;">Beginning with payments in 2011 (for tax years beginning in 2010), the farmland preservation credit was revised and expanded and the farmland tax relief credit was eliminated. For taxable years beginning after December 31, 2009, no new claims may be filed for the farmland preservation credit as it existed under prior law, but if an otherwise eligible claimant is subject to a farmland preservation agreement that was in effect on July 1, 2010, the claimant may continue to file claims for credits under the prior law until the farmland preservation agreement expires. A taxpayer who files a claim for the prior credit may not file a claim for the new credit.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://dairymarkets.org/cdp/CDP%20Newsletter,%20June.pdf" target="_blank">Read More</a></p>', 'Farmland Preservation & Farmland Tax Relief Credits', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'farmland-preservation-farmland-tax-relief-credits__trashed', '', '', '2017-03-18 01:11:18', '2017-03-18 01:11:18', '', 0, 'http://dairymarkets/?p=4', 0, 'post', '', 0),
